OL,6,FDiethylstilbestrol, commonly known as
OL,7,FDES, was a synthetic hormone
OL,8,Fprescribed to dry up breast milk and
OL,9,Frecommended for use in mother and baby
OL,10,Fhomes in England for decades.
OL,12,FIn the 40 years after World War Two,
OL,13,Fan estimated 200,000 unmarried mothers
OL,14,Fgave birth in these institutions run
OL,15,Fby the church or state and were
OL,16,Fpressured to put their babies up for
OL,17,Fadoption.
