OL,6,FYet in UK, the true extent of the harm
OL,7,Fcaused and the numbers exposed to DES
OL,8,Fis still unknown partly due to a lack
OL,9,Fof medical records. It's been
OL,10,Fdescribed by some doctors as 'the
OL,11,Fsilent thalidomide.'
OL,13,FDr Wael Agur, a Consultant
OL,14,FUrogynaecologist and advisor to the
OL,15,FScottish Government, has treated women
OL,16,Fwho were exposed to the drug.
OL,18,F"The most serious risk is the cancer
OL,19,Frisk," he told ITV Tonight. "This drug
OL,20,Fincreases the risk of breast cancer
OL,21,Fin the women who took it.
